1.00	RWC2007	2007 Rugby World Cup	The 2007 Rugby World Cup was the sixth Rugby World Cup, a quadrennial international rugby union competition inaugurated in 1987. Twenty nations competed for the Webb Ellis Cup in the tournament, which was hosted by France from 7 September to 20 October. France won the hosting rights in 2003, beating a bid from England. The competition consisted of 48 matches over 44 days; 42 matches were played in ten cities throughout France, as well as four in Cardiff, Wales, and two in Edinburgh, Scotland.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/9/92/RWC2007logo.svg/220px-RWC2007logo.svg.png
